{
  "info": {
    "name": "Vault-Tec SecDevOps — API Tests",
    "description": "Colección de pruebas funcionales y de seguridad para la API de Vault-Tec SecDevOps.\n\nEstructura:\n  P0 · Setup          — obtiene tokens y los guarda en variables\n  P1 · Autenticación  — A07: credenciales, rate limit, JWT\n  P2 · Acceso RBAC    — A01: roles overseer/dweller\n  P3 · Directivas     — CRUD de proyectos desde MySQL\n  P4 · Administración — usuarios, logs, estadísticas\n  P5 · Seguridad HTTP — A05: cabeceras OWASP\n  P6 · Smoke tests    — flujo feliz end-to-end\n\nVariables de colección:\n  base_url       → http://localhost:5000  (frontend proxy)\n  overseer_token → (auto) JWT del overseer\n  dweller_token  → (auto) JWT del dweller",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000"
    },
    {
      "key": "overseer_token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "dweller_token",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "P0 · Setup — obtener tokens",
      "description": "Ejecutar primero. Guarda los tokens JWT en variables de colección.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login overseer → guardar token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"username\":\"overseer\",\"password\":\"Overseer2077!\"}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('[Setup] Login overseer: 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('[Setup] Token JWT presente', () => pm.expect(j.token).to.be.a('string').and.have.lengthOf.above(10));",
                  "pm.test('[Setup] Rol admin confirmado', () => pm.expect(j.role).to.eql('admin'));",
                  "if (j.token) pm.environment.set('overseer_token', j.token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login dweller → guardar token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"username\":\"dweller\",\"password\":\"Dweller2077!\"}"
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('[Setup] Login dweller: 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('[Setup] Rol user confirmado', () => pm.expect(j.role).to.eql('user'));",
                  "if (j.token) pm.environment.set('dweller_token', j.token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
